relate-db

USAGE
  relate db create <db>
  relate db drop <db>
  relate db truncate <db>
  relate db list [--format=<format>|--ids]
  relate db start <db>
  relate db stop <db>
  relate db clone <db> <name|path|url>
  relate db backup <db> [name|path|url]
  relate db backups [path|url]
  relate db restore <name|path|url> <name>
  relate db exec <db> [<cypher-query>|--file=<path>]

OPTIONS
  --format=<format>       Specify what information should be returned.
  --ids                   Return only IDs.
  --file=<path>           Specify path to file to be executed.

NOTES
  exec:
    The query can be read from STDIN if not specified as an argument.
    If the query is specified the result is returned on STDOUT and the program is terminated.
    If the query is not specified (not even from STDIN), then an interactive shell is opened on the selected DB.

CONTEXT
  It has to be run in the context of a DBMS.
